
Overview of noun idealisation

The noun idealisation has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                 
1. idealization, idealisation -- ((psychiatry) a defense mechanism that splits something you are ambivalent about into two representations--one good and one bad)
2. idealization, idealisation -- (something that exists only as an idea)
3. idealization, idealisation, glorification -- (a portrayal of something as ideal; "the idealization of rural life was very misleading")
